Israeli Stocks: Bezeq, Hot Telecommunication, Israel Chemicals

-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 
2011-09-22T14:47:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/israeli-stocks-bezeq-hot-telecommunication-israel-chemicals.html
Israel ’s TA-25 Index declined the
most since Sept. 4, sliding 4.3 percent to 1,038.91 at the 4:30
p.m. close in Tel Aviv, bringing the index’s weekly drop to  1.7
percent. Investors traded about 1.32 billion shekels ($355
million) of shares and convertible securities today, according
to Tel Aviv Stock Exchange data.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Bezeq Israeli Telecommunication Corp. (BEZQ IT) retreated
the most in three days, declining 4.6 percent to 6.90 shekels. A
government appointed panel will recommend cutting or abolishing
the fees charged by Israel’s largest communications company and
 Hot Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT)   for calling between
networks, TheMarker reported.  The panel is finalizing its recommendations and will submit
them to the Ministry of Communications, Yechiel Shabi, a
ministry spokesman, said by phone today.  Hot, the second-biggest fixed-line operator, lost 2.8
percent to 46.18 shekels.  Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL)   plunged 8.3 percent, the
most since July 2009, to 43.25 shekels. The shares of the
company that extracts minerals from the  Dead Sea  to make
fertilizer declined as the price of commodities fell.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
 ssolomon22@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  